<section id="services-hero-532"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-patios-2-433d6b82.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Hardscaping Contractors</span><h1 class="cs-title">Hardscaping Services <span class="cs-color">Las Cruces, NM</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">Patios, walkways, retaining walls, and fire features built by our in-house crews. Every hardscaping project comes with a workmanship guarantee.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><img alt="Custom flagstone walkway hardscaping project by Brainard's Greenscapes in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-4-33defc6d.jpeg" height="636" width="480" loading="lazy"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Hardscaping and Landscaping</span><h2 class="cs-title">The Structural Foundation of a Great Outdoor Space</h2><p class="cs-text">What is hardscaping? It’s the stone, pavers, concrete, and masonry that give your yard shape and structure. While plants bring color, hardscaping creates the bones: patios for gathering, walkways for flow, retaining walls for grade changes, and fire features for year-round enjoyment. In Las Cruces, where summer highs top 100°F and caliche soil sits just inches below the surface, hardscaping installation demands careful base work and desert-tested materials. Our in-house crew handles every step, from excavation to final sealing.</p><ul class="cs-bullets"><li>Hardscaping pavers and flagstone patios on compacted base for decades of crack-free use.</li><li>Engineered retaining walls that control erosion, manage drainage, and create usable tiers.</li><li>Custom fire pits, outdoor fireplaces, and kitchen foundations built to code.</li><li>Walkways, borders, and seat walls that connect your entire property.</li></ul><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-pavers.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title"><a href="/services/hardscaping/pavers/">Pavers</a></h3><p class="cs-item-text">Concrete and natural-stone pavers installed over a properly compacted aggregate base. Interlocking, polymeric-sand-set, and built to handle freeze-thaw cycles and monsoon runoff.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-walkways.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title"><a href="/services/hardscaping/walkways/">Walkways</a></h3><p class="cs-item-text">Slip-resistant flagstone, paver, and decomposed-granite walkways. Front entry, side yard, and garden paths graded for proper drainage and built for daily traffic.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-stone-borders.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title"><a href="/services/hardscaping/stone-borders/">Stone Borders</a></h3><p class="cs-item-text">Mortared and dry-stacked stone edging that defines beds, contains mulch and gravel, and stops erosion. Local sandstone, flagstone, and cobble.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-patios.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title"><a href="/services/hardscaping/patios/">Patios</a></h3><p class="cs-item-text">Paver, flagstone, and stamped-concrete patios installed on 6+ inches of compacted aggregate. Built for entertaining, dining, and daily use in the desert heat.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-driveways.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title"><a href="/services/hardscaping/driveways/">Driveways</a></h3><p class="cs-item-text">Paver and concrete driveways engineered for the weight of vehicles and the freeze-thaw range of southern New Mexico. Proper subbase, drainage, and edge restraints.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-signs-870"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> About Brainard's Greenscapes</span><h2 class="cs-title">Signs You Need Professional Hardscaping</h2><p class="cs-text">Plants alone can’t solve structural problems. If any of these describe your yard, it’s time to call hardscaping contractors who know Las Cruces’s soil and climate.</p></div><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div><ul class="cs-signs"><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Water Pooling Near Your Foundation</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Standing water after monsoon rains is more than a nuisance. It erodes soil, damages foundations, and kills plants. Retaining walls and proper grading solve this for good.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">No Defined Outdoor Living Area</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">A backyard with no patio, no seating area, and no clear purpose is wasted square footage. A hardscaping patio creates an outdoor room you will actually use 8+ months a year in Las Cruces.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Cracked Concrete or Shifting Pavers</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Las Cruces’s caliche soil and 30–50°F daily temperature swings cause poorly installed surfaces to crack and heave. Professional base work prevents repeat failures and trip hazards.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Unusable Slopes and Awkward Corners</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Side yards, hillsides, and odd-shaped lots feel like dead space until hardscaping designs turn them into terraced gardens, pathways, or seating areas.</p></li></ul></div><img alt="Brainard's Greenscapes stone border hardscaping project in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-3-f534a194.jpeg" height="844" width="616" loading="lazy"></div></section><section id="services-process-148"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> How We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Our Hardscaping Process</h2></div><div class="cs-grid-wrap"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">On-Site Survey</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We walk your property, measure grades, test soil compaction, and locate utilities. You share your hardscaping ideas, and we match them to your site’s conditions and budget.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Material Selection</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Choose from hardscaping pavers, natural stone, masonry block, or stamped concrete. We bring samples to your property so you can compare hardscaping materials in your own light and setting.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Excavation &amp; Base</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We dig down to stable soil, lay 4–6 inches of compacted aggregate, and install edge restraints. This invisible base work is what keeps surfaces level and crack-free for decades.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Build &amp; Finish</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Our crew sets every paver, stone, and cap by hand. We seal joints, backfill edges, and clean the site so your new space is ready to enjoy on reveal day.</p></li></ul><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-up.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-3"></div></div></section><section id="services-why-353"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-6201bd97.jpeg" height="1861" width="1920" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper">Built to Last</span><h2 class="cs-title">Why Choose Brainard's Greenscapes for Hardscaping</h2><p class="cs-intro">A hardscaping patio or retaining wall is a one-time investment that should last 25+ years. Poorly installed work cracks, shifts, and costs more to fix than to build right the first time. Here’s what sets our hardscaping services apart from other contractors in Las Cruces.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-pavers-5-396126dc.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-concrete-patios-5-da71b859.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Desert-Engineered Base Work</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Las Cruces’s caliche soil and extreme heat demand deeper excavation and thicker aggregate bases than most regions. We dig to stable ground and compact in lifts so surfaces stay level through years of temperature swings.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Premium Hardscaping Materials</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">We source commercial-grade pavers, natural hardscaping stone, and masonry block rated for UV exposure and freeze-thaw cycles. These materials hold their color and strength for decades, not seasons.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">In-House Crews, No Subcontractors</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Our own masons and hardscape installers handle every project from start to finish. No handoffs, no miscommunication, no strangers showing up at your door. You deal with one team the entire time.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Workmanship Guarantee</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Every hardscaping installation is backed by our workmanship guarantee. If it shifts, settles, or fails under normal use, we come back and make it right at no cost to you.</p></li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-quote-button">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></section><section id="services-pricing-219"><div class="cs-container"><article class="cs-price-card"><h2 class="cs-price-title">Hardscaping Cost for Your Project</h2><span class="cs-price-label">Starting At</span> <span class="cs-price-amount"><span class="cs-price-symbol">$</span>3,000</span><p class="cs-price-text">Hardscaping cost depends on the size, materials, and features you choose. A simple paver walkway starts around $3,000. A full hardscaping patio with fire feature and retaining walls typically runs $8,000–$25,000+. Every project is scoped to your property and budget.</p><ul class="cs-price-bullets"><li>Engineered base work and proper drainage included</li><li>Premium pavers, natural stone, or masonry block</li><li>Workmanship guarantee on every project</li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-price-link">Request a Custom Quote <svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></a></article><article class="cs-diff-card"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-200d3afb.jpeg" height="581" width="572" loading="lazy"><h2 class="cs-diff-title">The Brainard’s Difference</h2><ul class="cs-diff-list"><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 V21"></path><path d="M8 8 H16"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Faith-Centered Values</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Honest pricing, clear timelines, and genuine care for your property. We treat your home the way we’d want ours treated.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 L20 6 V12 C20 16.5 16.5 20 12 21 C7.5 20 4 16.5 4 12 V6 Z"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Guaranteed Craftsmanship</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Workmanship guarantee on labor, plus manufacturer warranties on every hardscaping material we install.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2 C8 2 5 5 5 9 C5 14 12 22 12 22 C12 22 19 14 19 9 C19 5 16 2 12 2 Z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"></circle></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Locally Rooted</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Born and raised in Las Cruces. We build for the caliche soils, extreme heat, and monsoon rains we know firsthand.</p></div></li></ul></article></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Hardscaping Questions</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What is hardscaping, and how is it different from landscaping?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Hardscaping refers to the non-living, structural elements of your yard: patios, walkways, retaining walls, fire pits, and seat walls. Landscaping covers the living elements like plants, trees, and turf. Most outdoor projects combine hardscaping and landscaping together for a complete result.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much does hardscaping cost in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Patio installation cost varies by size and materials. A basic paver walkway starts around $3,000. A 300-square-foot patio runs $6,000–$12,000. Larger projects with retaining walls, fire features, and multiple zones can range from $15,000 to $30,000+. We provide a detailed, line-item quote at your free on-site estimate.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What hardscaping materials work best in the desert?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Interlocking pavers and natural stone are the top choices for Las Cruces. They handle extreme heat, UV exposure, and temperature swings without cracking or fading. Stamped concrete is another option at a lower price point. We bring samples to your property so you can compare colors, textures, and costs in person.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How long does a hardscaping installation take?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>A standard patio takes 3–5 days from excavation to finished surface. Walkways typically run 1–3 days. Larger projects with retaining walls, fire features, or multiple hardscaping zones may take 1–2 weeks. We give you a timeline at your estimate so you know what to expect.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What are some popular hardscaping ideas for backyard spaces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>The most popular hardscaping ideas for backyard projects in Las Cruces include paver patios with built-in seating, fire pit gathering areas, flagstone pathways through xeriscape beds, and terraced retaining walls on sloped lots. Outdoor kitchen foundations and pergola footings are also common requests. We can sketch out hardscaping designs during your free estimate.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you handle permits for hardscaping projects?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>We guide you through any permit requirements and can prepare documentation for HOA submissions. Most residential hardscaping in Las Cruces does not require a permit. However, retaining walls above a certain height or work near utility easements may need one. We will let you know up front during your estimate.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-related-184"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Related Services</span><h2 class="cs-title">Complete Your Outdoor Project</h2><p class="cs-text">Hardscaping and landscaping go hand in hand. Add <a href="/services/landscaping/">landscaping</a> around your new patio, connect <a href="/services/irrigation/">irrigation &amp; sprinkler</a> zones to new planting beds, or protect your investment with a <a href="/services/landscape-maintenance/">landscape maintenance</a> plan. We also offer full <a href="/services/landscape-design/">landscape design</a> and <a href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/">xeriscaping</a> for water-wise outdoor spaces.</p></div></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Let's Talk About Your Landscape</h2><a href="/contact/" class="cs-talk-button">Contact Us</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-grass"></section>
